this is not how spider work

The large ass-part of a bug -- spider, mantis, whatever -- is called the ABDOMEN. Thorax is the midbody, divided up into prothorax, mesothorax, and metathorax on insects. Spiders don't have a thorax, they have a cephalothorax, where the head and the midbody are the same part.
